# Public RFP repository boundary

`WindhorseTour/wht-2026-retheme-rfp` is the **public bidding** repo only.

## Correct vs forbidden paths

| Use | Path |
|-----|------|
| **Private procurement (ONLY here)** | `/Users/hggreenberg/Development/wht-2026-retheme-procurement/` |
| **Public RFP (this repo)** | `/Users/hggreenberg/Development/wht-2026-retheme-rfp/` |

**FORBIDDEN — never create, write, copy, or mkdir:**

`/Users/hggreenberg/Development/wht-2026-retheme-rfp/wht-2026-retheme-procurement/`

That nested folder was a historical agent mistake. `.gitignore` hides it from git but **the folder must not exist on disk** in the RFP repo. If you see it, **delete it** (`rm -rf wht-2026-retheme-procurement`) and write to the sibling repo instead.

Do not use a combined Cursor workspace that nests procurement inside the RFP tree.

## Never add, copy, link, or commit

- The `wht-2026-retheme-procurement/` directory **inside this repo** (or any nested clone)
- Vendor scorecards, vendor notes, or files under `vendors/` from procurement
- Executed/signed NDAs (`*EXECUTED*.pdf`, signed PDFs, signature certificates)
- Vendor proposals, bid analysis, or correspondence meant for internal evaluation
- README or docs links to the private procurement repo or its GitHub URL
- Paths like `documents/nda/`, `documents/proposals/` when they contain evaluation material

## Allowed here

- Public RFP, Q&A log, reference files, NDA **template** (`03-legal/NDA-template.md`), commercial template, workflow docs

## Before any git commit or push

1. Confirm `wht-2026-retheme-procurement/` does **not** exist in this repo root.
2. Run `git status` and inspect every added/changed path.
3. If any path matches the forbidden list above, **stop** — do not commit or push.
4. Do not use `git add -f` to bypass `.gitignore` for procurement or evaluation files.

## If asked to log vendor NDAs, proposals, scores, or evaluation work

**Refuse in this repo.** Write only to `/Users/hggreenberg/Development/wht-2026-retheme-procurement/`.
